'''Madcap Theater''' is a shortform [[improvisational theatre|improvisational comedy]] group located in [[Westminster, Colorado]]. Opened in 2006 by improv actors Russ Faillaci and Brian Harper, the group performs weekly improv shows and offers improv classes.<ref>[http://www.madcapimprov.com/newsupdates/1-latest-news/61-articlequickwittedfamily.html "Quick-witted family?] Colorado Lifestyles, September 2007. Retrieved 01-08-2009.</ref> In 2007, 2008, and 2009, it was voted Denver's best live comedy venue by ABC Channel 7.<ref>[http://kmgh.cityvoter.com/madcap-theater/biz/35317 "The 2007 A-List"], Channel 7 news</ref> Unique from many other [[List of improvisational theatre companies|improvisational comedy groups]], '''Madcap''' performs family-friendly, clean comedy.<ref>Josh Ortega, [http://www.madcapimprov.com/newsupdates/1-latest-news/58-articleimprovcomedy.html "Improv Comedy"], Colorado Lifestyles Magazine, Retrieved 01-08-2009</ref><ref>Evie Hemphill [http://www.madcapimprov.com/newsupdates/1-latest-news/60-articlebeyondthescript.html "Beyond the Script"], The Westminster Window. Retrieved 01-08-2009</ref>
